        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "90e3caf9-26bd-4adf-aebc-954075539ba2",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "1. "
        },
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "Purpose"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "16f99728-4c44-4cf5-80a8-7b0477e68b9e",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The purpose of this Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) is to define a controlled process for implementing and managing changes in products, processes, documents, and systems in compliance with ISO13485. This ensures that all changes are reviewed, documented, approved, and assessed for their impact on quality, safety, and regulatory compliance."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "73daea9c-3ff3-4dc3-a798-e88a64a77d34",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "fa831e16-b4e5-49e8-bd94-b505a00faef7",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "2. "
        },
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "Scope"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "f55739dd-7727-4798-a86e-e71589159701",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "This SOP applies to all employees involved in the design, development, manufacturing, and post-market surveillance of medical devices or other regulated products. It includes changes to production processes, materials, equipment, suppliers, documents, and any changes impacting the quality management system."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "f0830c41-5f12-4a9a-b30f-c94d93ebab36",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "34a98785-1922-4b08-a872-e2981e2df359",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "3. "
        },
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "Responsibilities"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "cd22c80b-0fc5-4513-96b5-dd0f0e281c15",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "20dbe1d6-cc5f-4507-bfe3-2a9666cd4583",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Change Requestor"
            },
            {
              "text": ": Initiates the change control request, providing initial documentation and justification for the change."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "82bf1f3a-ccae-4ca6-916f-836e2b8876fc",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "0bf49b3d-0c6f-4012-944e-4757099cf686",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Quality Assurance (QA)"
            },
            {
              "text": ": Reviews and assesses the change for compliance with ISO13485, performs risk and impact assessments, and confirms validation requirements."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "e0ad95e6-7205-478e-b5f1-51bc48667a87",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "33c7c4ea-b5f4-4d04-87e4-37b809a1b142",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Department Heads"
            },
            {
              "text": ": Approve changes related to their areas and ensure resources are available for implementation."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "13bb57fb-236e-4ede-9ee2-171d83976923",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "00906631-a413-4990-b843-8437c73bed8e",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Regulatory Affairs"
            },
            {
              "text": ": Reviews changes for regulatory impact and coordinates necessary notifications to regulatory bodies."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "a03bb673-ccec-41c5-8752-f80affe03edb",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "8301eb1a-8781-4a73-bbbc-fdd9d75d14cd",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Management"
            },
            {
              "text": ": Provides final approval for changes impacting quality, safety, or regulatory compliance."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "fbf8da95-176d-4702-b241-cc2447e154d2",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "735db142-bcd5-42e0-8446-cb398d31dd00",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "4. "
        },
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "Definitions"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "4e88d3f8-4d5b-42bd-94e4-a800fb8d86ef",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "f21410e0-53c7-4335-9c09-09409a6ae22b",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Change Control"
            },
            {
              "text": ": A structured process used to ensure any modifications to products, processes, systems, or documents are documented, reviewed, and approved."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "32375ca1-7def-4ca8-99fd-a31ff7a73917",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "a021b050-6a31-40eb-ac3e-54246f0495e7",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Impact Assessment"
            },
            {
              "text": ": An evaluation of the change's effect on quality, safety, regulatory compliance, and related processes or products."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "904b567f-3981-4424-9903-4c171fd56d18",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "4544426d-1488-4327-bc04-d8cecaf4ae3f",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "5. "
        },
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "General Change Control Guidelines"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c303eaf8-d71b-43e0-8f80-17dabc20e059",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "2b676393-0e28-4b8d-8a28-7679b23e25c1",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Initiation"
            },
            {
              "text": ": All changes must be initiated by completing a Change Control Form (CCF)."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "71971038-8b82-493d-8c2b-2a68594e7687",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "e433ccbb-db25-4103-bc28-f4c474175d10",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Documentation"
            },
            {
              "text": ": Each change must be documented, including rationale, impact assessment, validation requirements, and approvals."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "80241b0d-6423-4d49-a588-641bf3f5471c",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "b9e42afd-0e08-44f6-8b82-78598750d3a2",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Approval"
            },
            {
              "text": ": Changes require multi-level approval based on impact; high-impact changes require management approval."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "8a3dccbd-a4a1-4543-b179-d537fd43ccbc",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "6fd8ea27-4c66-499c-a7dd-1b643ad56e27",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "6. "
        },
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "Change Control Process"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "439f6816-6bb3-495c-8416-6492c884e69b",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "10932eeb-0111-4e50-be2a-15ffdeb9459d",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "6.1. Initiating a Change Control Request"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c9f356ea-b613-4296-9674-a6700a076ded",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "e31f43b8-9b98-4328-b8ba-29664447534f",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The Change Requestor completes a Change Control Form (CCF) with details, including description, justification, and proposed effective date."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d99ffdbc-d629-4ebc-824f-d4a3fc30c849",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "bed62ecb-0a20-47d1-b182-06268227fbaa",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The CCF is submitted to QA for initial review."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ea0a3933-5f22-4fce-9fa2-89d607a20d9c",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "2c37b62b-a51f-491c-8650-b7e886677386",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "6.2. QA Review and Impact Assessment"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "2f1f278a-bba5-44cc-8ff9-fb49339d82d5",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "4c503aa6-2895-43ea-a5f0-9d5ecc37cf03",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Document and Regulatory Review"
            },
            {
              "text": ": QA reviews the change for ISO13485 compliance and assesses its impact on controlled documents and regulatory requirements."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "1c7911d3-91b7-406a-83f1-fbabbdfd11de",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "cf2234cf-b41b-4fff-9d93-bf13d3e5b41f",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Risk Assessment"
            },
            {
              "text": ": QA performs a risk assessment to identify any potential risks associated with the change."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "3525ed95-bb09-4bab-a271-4f4c0fb43bb4",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "706c1557-604e-4491-b04b-375b0cbede83",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Validation Requirements"
            },
            {
              "text": ": QA determines if validation or verification activities are required."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "48acf144-cc6f-4867-93ee-1413e787f18d",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "b538ba25-faff-441b-ab43-c1a32b71634f",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Training and Competency"
            },
            {
              "text": ": QA evaluates if additional training is necessary for affected personnel."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "f165bb59-4e95-423c-a225-e1d7e9231140",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "8e11d077-e7fc-4f62-b806-e82a8680763f",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "6.3. Regulatory Affairs Review"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "69368b27-50f6-479c-b047-0a8385d9d9d2",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "e0ebbf74-d567-4596-8d1d-e823590a1ba8",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Regulatory Impact"
            },
            {
              "text": ": Regulatory Affairs assesses whether the change requires notification to regulatory bodies."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "12e41f0f-ab6d-41b9-942a-5b19b3314f7f",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "b669fe0e-4b6d-4b32-be41-3c6f14ec7b15",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "If submission is necessary, Regulatory Affairs coordinates the documentation and approvals."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c9a20e02-d34d-4248-b453-9182e90547ca",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "1883d399-8791-414b-a8d5-570a00b946cf",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "6.4. Approval Process"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "23f67299-9189-4ad6-bb2b-bd79749a738c",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "94cbd18e-a080-4a34-b4ea-2a3b66596422",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The completed CCF and supporting documents are circulated to relevant Department Heads for approval."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "4bf9af23-0971-4741-9ffe-865266bc86e2",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "9ea1d220-dcd7-44f8-8cf0-c4bb2e8063d6",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Management Approval"
            },
            {
              "text": ": Changes impacting quality, safety, or compliance must receive final management approval."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "15f86f7f-0ab9-4b8e-83b5-b808c38b014d",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "aedfad0b-4716-4dea-9b4b-78fe6b8c63dd",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Upon approval, QA updates all relevant controlled documents."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "35676fa9-18d0-4898-b913-53e88a5b2da0",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "64e5da7b-9af9-4c39-af6c-f2eef03e3da1",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "6.5. Implementation of Change"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "f78e9c20-b00b-40cf-97c0-29b38b3f5d34",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "2711ddae-2eed-4943-9c14-391bd46761e2",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Resource Allocation"
            },
            {
              "text": ": Department Heads allocate necessary resources and responsibilities."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c2961f6b-1fb1-4b19-bee2-97194c87dd2b",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "cb25b67c-3783-406e-93a7-04fa9267b042",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Training and Communication"
            },
            {
              "text": ": QA ensures that affected personnel are notified and trained."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ad8af261-bdaf-49f1-ac88-9337d4bad950",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "5e5ba85e-5ce9-42c0-a5e1-4f84463c9b23",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Timeline"
            },
            {
              "text": ": QA ensures implementation is conducted per the approved timeline, completing any validation activities."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "6dec06b1-e8cf-41c6-bf47-aec6269cad7c",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "a047e056-e7c1-4628-aba0-14e928e25eeb",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "6.6. Post-Implementation Review"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "baff3d99-3ecc-45a8-aa99-bb61fe2a2ccd",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "ccb7863b-2603-4b4a-ab1d-913dc62c6e83",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "QA conducts a review to confirm all objectives were met without adverse effects on quality, safety, or compliance."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "41f66bd5-fa98-4899-a5e2-d2a730a8d658",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "11ee82b4-097e-4a19-b5f3-303b8744399b",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Any additional findings are documented, and further actions are identified if necessary."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "a6060707-99bc-4a03-a23b-5d93b2751cf8",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "4659396f-1a70-4e52-9238-771a688667f2",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "QA closes the Change Control in the Change Control log once completed."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "9659c249-29dd-4781-898c-41d2c36b3e1c",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "5143f479-be0b-43e5-b920-1f0f9529804a",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "7. "
        },
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "Documentation and Record Keeping"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c771f157-b4aa-4b00-80f8-9fc81c0247f0",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "39f32ed9-cac2-41ed-935d-e6be4cdf7b2c",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Change Control Records"
            },
            {
              "text": ": The completed CCF, risk assessments, regulatory submissions, training records, and validation documentation are retained in accordance with Document Control procedures."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "4f5b7443-f11d-4c63-ba11-e081ed6a7dce",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "35ae47c9-0563-4658-9aa0-54ed2b3c2e24",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "Accessibility"
            },
            {
              "text": ": All records must be accessible for audits and retained per ISO13485 requirements."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "3426ef23-a447-43b7-bc98-b938b71b7f26",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d135fe4b-9512-40d3-8778-2095db8c69d6",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "8. "
        },
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "Training"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "28dcccb6-c87f-4f75-8fe3-3ee87de3434c",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "20737def-2dc6-4449-a99b-2319e02ed5e0",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "All relevant personnel must receive training on this Change Control SOP before initiating or managing any changes."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "6e78c0f7-50b5-4952-97a3-b1e0624c4b87",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "519f5c20-4f4f-43a8-9fa9-95597d6c3b7b",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Refresher training is conducted annually or when significant updates are made to the SOP."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "8026b7dc-7b35-406c-abc9-3c9428aec4d3",
      "type": "li",
      "indent": 0,
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "b495ff1f-16cb-4c29-8b1d-6ed9a160061e",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Training records are maintained for auditing purposes."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "b13f581c-8896-4986-9536-f27f2a983484",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
